column3: {{c1::the}} - "used to refer to something already mentioned"
{{c1::be}} - "To exist; to be alive; used to give information about someone or something"
{{c1::and}} - "used to refer to two or more things"
{{c1::of}} - "belonging to or connected with something"
{{c1::to}} - "move towards; in the direction of"
{{c1::a}} - "one (of something)"
{{c1::in}} - "being inside something"
{{c1::have}} - "to own, possess, or hold something"
{{c1::it}} - "a thing that has been previously mentioned"
{{c1::you}} - "person someone is speaking or writing to"
{{c1::he}} - "object form of a male person you are talking about"
{{c1::for}} - "used to show the purpose, or need of something"
{{c1::they}} - "used to refer to two or more people, animals, or things"
{{c1::not}} - "word indicating the negative of verbs, adjectives, etc."
{{c1::that}} - "used to show which person or thing we are talking about"
{{c1::we}} - "used to refer to the speaker and other people together"
{{c1::on}} - "located on the surface of something (e.g., a table or wall)"
{{c1::with}} - "used to express that people or things are together"
{{c1::this}} - "person, thing, or idea near you"
{{c1::I}} - "the person who is speaking or writing"
{{c1::do}} - "to act; to perform actions"
{{c1::as}} - "a word used to compare two equal things"
{{c1::at}} - "in the place where something is"
{{c1::she}} - "female person or animal mentioned before"
{{c1::but}} - "used before you say something different, opposite"
{{c1::from}} - "starting at a particular place, time, or level"
{{c1::by}} - "near; with"
{{c1::will}} - "used with verbs to express the future"
{{c1::or}} - "used to link alternatives, to introduce another choice"
{{c1::say}} - "to use words to tell a message"
{{c1::go}} - "to move or travel to another place"
{{c1::so}} - "for that reason"
{{c1::all}} - "completely; totally"
{{c1::if}} - "introducing a condition for something to happen"
{{c1::one}} - "number 1"
{{c1::would}} - "modal verb used to indicate possibility, request, etc."
{{c1::about}} - "of (a subject); concerning"
{{c1::can}} - "to be able to; have the skill to; have the time to"
{{c1::which}} - "question word to ask about a person's choice"
{{c1::there}} - "in that place or position, at that location"
{{c1::know}} - "to have knowledge of things in your mind"
{{c1::more}} - "greater in amount, number, or size"
{{c1::get}} - "to obtain, receive, or be given something"
{{c1::who}} - "what or which person or people, to ask about, talking about"
{{c1::like}} - "to find something pleasing; to prefer something"
{{c1::when}} - "word you use to ask about the time or day"
{{c1::think}} - "to have an idea, opinion, or belief about something"
{{c1::make}} - "to create something by putting things together"
{{c1::time}} - "something measured in minutes, hours, days, etc."
{{c1::see}} - "to use your eyes to look at something"
{{c1::what}} - "asking for information about someone or something"
{{c1::up}} - "move higher; raise"
{{c1::some}} - "used to refer to a person or thing that is not known"
{{c1::other}} - "something else; not the first one"
{{c1::out}} - "away from the inside or center"
{{c1::good}} - "excellent; high quality"
{{c1::people}} - "human beings in general; plural of person"
{{c1::year}} - "unit of time equal to 12 months"
{{c1::take}} - "to pick up something and go away with it"
{{c1::no}} - "being none; not having or being"
{{c1::well}} - "in a good way"
{{c1::because}} - "for a reason"
{{c1::very}} - "much; great in amount"
{{c1::just}} - "only; a short time ago"
{{c1::come}} - "to move toward someone; go with someone"
{{c1::could}} - "used as the past form of can, to show possibility"
{{c1::work}} - "activity you do in order to make money"
{{c1::use}} - "to do something with, for a task or purpose"
{{c1::than}} - "used when comparing two things"
{{c1::now}} - "at the present time or moment"
{{c1::then}} - "at that time not now"
{{c1::also}} - "in addition; too; in a similar way"
{{c1::into}} - "going inside something"
{{c1::only}} - "just one; just that amount or thing; not more than"
{{c1::look}} - "to turn your eyes in a particular direction"
{{c1::want}} - "to desire or wish for something; hope for a thing"
{{c1::give}} - "to hand over or present something to someone"
{{c1::first}} - "coming before all others in time or place"
{{c1::new}} - "not old, recently born, built, or made"
{{c1::way}} - "how something is done"
{{c1::find}} - "to discover something by looking for it"
{{c1::over}} - "above; across; more than; on the other side"
{{c1::any}} - "one (thing) of many; some (thing)"
{{c1::after}} - "later than another time, or behind something"
{{c1::day}} - "a period of 24 hours"
{{c1::where}} - "word you use to ask the location of something"
{{c1::thing}} - "something you cannot remember the name of"
{{c1::most}} - "nearly all of something"
{{c1::should}} - "used to indicate what is proper or reasonable"
{{c1::need}} - "to be unable to manage without something; require"
{{c1::much}} - "a lot; large amount; a high degree of"
{{c1::right}} - "on side where the hand that most people write with"
{{c1::how}} - "in what way something happens or is done"
{{c1::back}} - "the place you were before"
{{c1::mean}} - "to have a particular meaning or value"
{{c1::even}} - "as well; too"
{{c1::may}} - "used to talk about what is possible"
{{c1::here}} - "in, at, or to this position or place"
{{c1::many}} - "used to refer to a large number of things"
{{c1::such}} - "like or similar"
